HEADWORD: Electrition
<hw>E`lec*tri"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The recognition by an animal body of the
electrical condition of external objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Electrization</ent>⟦br⟧
